http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Tragedy-at-farmland/article13978172.ece

A farmer died of electrocution in his agriculture field near Vallapuram village in Mudigonda mandal on Saturday evening.Sources said that E. Nageswara Rao, 40, of Vallapuram, suffered an electric shock when he came in contact with a live wire connected to the motor pumpset in his agricultural field in the evening.He died instantaneously. The local farmers noticed his body lying along a tractor close to a pumpset in the agriculture field on the outskirts of the village late in the evening.He is survived by his wife and two children.The Mudigonda police registered a case and are investigating.